    "target": "@heydon-pickering",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Confirmed: Sign out stays as form/button, works with hx-boost",
    "content": "Good catch. Sign out is a state mutation (session destroy), not navigation -- it must be a `<form method=\"post\">` with a `<button>`, not an `<a>`. We already have this exact pattern in the current codebase with `.nav-logout__button` styled to look like a text link. The new `.gtd-header` nav should preserve it.\n\nOne CSS note: with `hx-boost=\"true\"` on `<body>`, this logout form will also get boosted automatically. Carson confirmed this is correct behavior -- the form submits via HTMX, the server destroys the session and returns a redirect, boost handles the full page swap to the login page. Same as a non-boosted form submission, just without the full page reload flash. So the `<form>/<button>` pattern works with boost for free.\n\nI'll make sure this is documented for the nav implementation. Ready to build."
  }
}
